30/10/2009
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Court of BiH sentenced Bosnian Serb Zoran Maric to 15 years in prison Thursday (October 29th) for war crimes committed in 1992 during the Bosnian conflict. Maric, a former member of the Bosnian Serb forces, was convicted of the illegal imprisonment and killing of Bosniak civilians in the Jajce municipality. He has admitted his guilt. (RTRS, BHRT, Fena, Reuters - 29/10/09)
